	<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/b5ce20c4688480e08187c2a253effaa8?s=48&amp;d=retro&amp;r=X' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />	<cite itemprop="name"><a itemprop='url' href='https://plus.google.com/114596829127383196272' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Richard King</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>	</div>

	<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a itemprop="url" href="http://ottopress.com/2010/wordpress-3-0-theme-tip-the-comment-form/comment-page-3/#comment-10995">
		<time itemprop="dateCreated" datetime="2012-06-26T10:18:30+00:00">June 26, 2012 at 10:18 am</time></a>	</div>

	<div itemprop="text"><p>Geir E and Albert,</p>
<p>you would add the onclick= to your search form. In twentyeleven you are looking for the file searchform.php.<br />
Copy the searchform.php from your twentyeleven theme folder and paste it into your child theme folder. That way when WordPress update twentyeleven it will update that searchform not your child theme searchform.</p>
<p>Richard</p>
</div>

